@startuml
title system_info — high-level sequence
actor User
participant Discord as "discord.py"
participant Bot as "DiscordBot (src/discord_bot.py)"
participant AsyncRoute as "ed_route_async"
participant Route as "ed_route"
participant Cache as "Ed_Cache (edgis_cache)"
database DB as "TinyDB (data/*.db)"
participant EDGIS as "EDGIS (external HTTP API)"

User -> Discord: sends `!system_info <name>` command
Discord -> Bot: dispatch command handler
Bot -> AsyncRoute: await get_system_info(name)
AsyncRoute -> Route: get_system_info(name)
Route -> DB: DB(db_filename) constructor / open
Route -> Cache: Ed_Cache(database)
Route -> Cache: find_system_info(name)
Cache -> DB: get_system(name)
alt cached
    DB --> Cache: return system_info
else not cached
    Cache -> EDGIS: HTTP GET /coords?q=<name>
    EDGIS --> Cache: JSON system_info
    Cache -> DB: insert_system(system_info)
end
Cache --> Route: system_info
Route --> AsyncRoute: return system_info
AsyncRoute --> Bot: system_info
Bot -> Discord: ctx.send("<name>: <system_info>")
@enduml
